    "text": "Erdős Problem #936: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Are\\[2^n\\pm 1\\]and\\[n!\\pm 1\\]powerful (i.e. if $p\\mid m$ then $p^2\\mid m$) for only finitely many $n$? Current best: Cushing and Pascoe \\cite{CuPa16} have shown the answer to the second question is yes assuming the abc conjecture - in fact, for any fixed $k\\geq 0$, there are only finitely many $n$ and powerful $x$ such that $\\lvert x-n!\\rvert \\leq k$. Prize: no. OEIS: A146968. Tags: number theory.",
